The paper proposes a deep-learning-based classification method for holographic memory data pages. The use of deep neural networks and multilayer perceptrons suggests that the paper may belong to the computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), or multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. The focus on classification and deep learning makes cs.CV and cs.LG the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.AI and cs.NE. The use of holographic memory suggests that cs.MM may also be a relevant sub-category.
